  "about": "Pokémon: Adventures in the Orange Islands is the second season of the Pokémon anime series and of Pokémon the Series: The Beginning, known in Japan as Pocket Monsters (ポケットモンスター, Poketto Monsutā). It originally aired in Japan from January 28 to October 7, 1999, on TV Tokyo, and in the United States from December 4, 1999, to October 14, 2000, on The WB/Kids' WB!.\nThe season follows Ash Ketchum as he travels across the Orange Islands to challenge its Pokémon League while joined by Misty and Tracey Sketchit, a Pokémon Watcher.\nThe episodes were directed by Masamitsu Hidaka and produced by the animation studio Oriental Light and Magic.",
